parameters:
\N<Man>Segi-san, where do you think you're going? I hate to think
it, but if you're planning to go to the ruins ahead, I'd
advise against it.

\N<Man>The entrance management of the ruins that have been in this
town for ages is now being handled by Luda's soldiers...

\N<Man>There are still factions within the city that attempt to
resist Luda's soldiers, but it's such a nuisance. I keep
saying we should avoid pointless conflicts...

\N<Man>Protective armor can be considered the bare minimum of
preparation, whether you're exploring ruins or fighting in
the training grounds.
\N<Hojiko>Answer me honestly, what were you doing here!? Eh!?

\N<Hojiko's Wife>Hmph... What's with the sudden interrogation! What I do and
where I do it is none of your business! Don't act like a
husband and interfere!

\N<Hojiko>I know... I know everything! You... You've been meeting a
man at this shop recently, haven't you...!? I know all about
it!

\N<Hojiko's Wife>So what if I have! You have no right to reproach me for such
things!

\N<Hojiko's Wife>If it bothers you, then try to sweep me off my feet! If you
can't even do that, I won't lend an ear to your worthless
words!
\N<Hojiko>Don't joke with me! Even if you're the one involved, I...!

\N<Hojiko>Oh, oh my... if it isn't Segi-san. You've caught me in quite
the situation... hehe.

\N<Hojiko>It's fine, our relationship has been cold for a long time.
As you can see, I'm such a failure of a husband that I can't
even keep my wife from going to her lover.

\N<Hojiko>Oops, but that's not to say I'm looking for sympathy in my
situation. Let's be completely fair here.
\N<Hojiko>By the way... did something happen to you, Segi-san?

\N<Hojiko>How should I put it... I can't quite express it well, but
today you seem unusually glamorous... No, well, you're
always beautiful, of course?

\N<Hojiko>Hmm... is that so. Well then, see you again at the training
session.

\N<Segi>Actually, I saw the request board at the management office,
Rozaro-san's.

\N<Rozaro>Request board? Ah, you mean the sparring partner thing. What
about it?
\N<Segi>...Well, I was wondering if I could be of any help?

\N<Segi>Yes, I am aware that I might not be strong enough to be your
sparring partner, Rozaro-san.

\N<Segi>But you have always been a great help to both my son and me,
and more than anything, it would serve as good training for
myself as well.

\N<Segi>I know it's selfish to offer to help with training when in
the end it's for my own benefit.
\N<Segi>But... what do you think? Can I be of any assistance to you?

\N<Rozaro>...Understood. Then I'll accept your offer without
reservation.
\N<Segi>Really? Thank you so much. I'll do my very best.

\N<Rozaro>Of course, I'll pay you for your time as a training partner.
But since it's training, I won't hold back. Is that alright
with you?

\N<Rozaro>Hmm, then let's begin in the forest outskirts as soon as
you're ready.
\N<Rozaro>Then, Segi-san, shall we start the training right away?

\N<Rozaro>...Segi-san, don't overdo it. You should rest a bit. You
can't handle me all at once.
\N<Segi>No, I'm fine... What should I... help with next...

\N<Rozaro>...I appreciate the sentiment. But if we've managed to find
this time, I want it to be meaningful for you too.

\N<Rozaro>In other words... this training should be beneficial for you
as well as for me.

\N<Rozaro>So from here on out, let's focus on training for your sake.
Consider it part of my request to you, is that okay?

\N<Rozaro>Don't thank me yet. Of course, I'll take it seriously since
I'm involved. Make sure you don't regret agreeing to train
with me.

\N<Rozaro>Hmm... listen, Segi-san. As a warrior who must fight, there
are several critical elements you're lacking.

\N<Rozaro>One is muscular strength, which is the source of power for
attacks. Another is physical strength, which is essential
for defense against attacks. And one more is vitality, the
source of life.

\N<Rozaro>All are important elements in battle. Now, what do you
consider important? I'll accompany you in any training you
wish to focus on.

\N<Segi>(Indeed, all the elements Rozaro-san mentioned seem
important... Which one should I choose...)

\N<Rozaro>You're focusing on muscular strength. Understood. Let's
proceed with today's training in that direction.

\N<Rozaro>Ah, it was good training for me too. And from now on, I plan
to regularly post requests at the management office.

\N<Rozaro>If you feel like it, please let me know again. I'm always
willing to help you.
\N<Segi>Yes. I'll be looking forward to it next time as well.

\N<Rozaro>You're focusing on physical strength. Understood. Let's
proceed with today's training in that direction.

\N<Rozaro>Ah, it was good training for me too. And from now on, I plan
to regularly post requests at the management office.

\N<Rozaro>If you feel like it, please let me know again. I'm always
willing to help you.
\N<Segi>Yes. I'll be looking forward to it next time as well.

\N<Rozaro>You're focusing on vitality. Understood. Let's proceed with
today's training in that direction.
\N<Segi>Haah... haah... ah, thank you... so much...

\N<Rozaro>Ah, it was good training for me too. And from now on, I plan
to regularly post requests at the management office.

\N<Rozaro>If you feel like it, please let me know again. I'm always
willing to help you.
\N<Segi>Yes. I'll be looking forward to it next time as well.
